1. define a function that gets the variable for the linear problem (takes a product as a variable)
    a. x = the product and states that the product must be at least 0
    b. return x
2. define a function to get the users input(takes no parameters)
    a. ask the user for what product they are selling
    b. return their input
3. define a function to get a constraint value
    a. ask the user what the constraint is for the given resource
    b. return their input
4. define a function to get the limitations of a resource
    a. ask the user what the limit is for the given resource
    b. return their input
5. define a function to get the profit for a product
    a. ask the user what the profit is for a given item
    b. return the profit
